# Rhino Player — Cursor / agent context (compact)

## Purpose

- **Rhino Player**: mpv-backed media player for Linux (GNOME, Ubuntu, and similar) with **GTK4 / libadwaita** UI, implemented in **Rust**, targeting a **statically linked** distributable when feasible.
- **Product context**: `docs/product-and-use-cases.md` (use cases and feature map). Behavior is specified in `docs/` first, then implemented. Copyright (C) 2026 Peter Adrianov; license `GPL-3.0-or-later` in root `LICENSE` / `COPYRIGHT` and the About dialog.

## Directories

- `build.rs` — Linux: embeds `DT_RUNPATH` for `/usr/local/lib/<multiarch>` and `/usr/local/lib` so a locally built `libmpv` (e.g. VapourSynth) is preferred over the distro copy without `LD_LIBRARY_PATH`. macOS: adds Homebrew `lib` to the linker search path for `libmpv.dylib`.
- `scripts/macos-dev-env.sh` — exports `PKG_CONFIG_PATH` and `PATH` for Homebrew GTK 4 / libadwaita before `cargo build` on macOS.
- `data/` — Freedesktop assets: `data/icons` (hicolor app PNGs + `scalable/actions/speedometer-symbolic.svg`, `source/*` design + `rebuild-png-assets.sh`; see `data/icons/README.md`), `data/vs` (bundled full-affinity `rhino_60_mvtools.vpy` — Linux loads `libmvtools.so`, macOS loads `libmvtools.dylib` via Homebrew; cached path in settings + `RHINO_MVTOOLS_LIB`; [VapourSynth](https://www.vapoursynth.com/) notes: `data/vs/README.md`), `data/applications/*.desktop`, `data/metainfo` (AppStream), `install-to-user-dirs.sh` (installs to `~/.local/share` for shell/taskbar icon). Index: `data/README.md`.
- `docs/` — Feature specs **before** implementation. Index: `docs/README.md`. One file per feature area under `docs/features/`. Product and use cases: `docs/product-and-use-cases.md`.
- `src/` — `main.rs` (entry + locale), `lib.rs` (`mod mpris` — Linux-only MPRIS2 `mpris-server` + GTK main-context task; snapshots from transport), `sched.rs` (Linux `ioprio_set` I/O *class* best-effort at startup—no `nice`; from `main` before GTK), `app.rs` (thin include hub + `APP_ID`), `app/` (GTK shell split by responsibility: base/run, load, mpv realize, transport events (`observe_property` drain), final actions, input, file actions, file-loaded hooks, recent undo, chrome/open/seek/tooltip/`build_window` (main-window **`GdkFileList`/`GFile`** drop, same **`on_open`** as menu Open), `GtkWindowHandle` video move, bottom prev/play/next + seek + times + **Close Video**, header sound/sub/speed/menu popovers, preferences, session **Exit After Current Video**, `db::init`, EOF sibling advance), `audio_tracks.rs` (mpv `track-list` + `aid`, radio list in sound popover), `icons.rs` (prepends manifest `data/icons` so app id + bundled symbolics resolve during `cargo run`), `db.rs` (SQLite `rhino.sqlite`: history, `settings` kv: `video_smooth_60` / `video_vs_path` / `video_mvtools_lib`, media duration/thumbs), `video_pref.rs` (optional VapourSynth `vf` from `db::VideoPrefs`, bundled `data/vs/rhino_60_mvtools.vpy`, mvtools cache + `RHINO_MVTOOLS_LIB` from `paths::mvtools_from_env` / `mvtools_lib_search`, `RHINO_SOURCE_FPS` from mpv `container-fps` so the script recovers cadence when mpv passes `0/0`), `mpv_embed.rs` + `mpv_embed/` (Linux: libmpv `RenderContext` bound to a [`gtk::GLArea`] via `gl_platform.rs` (EGL/GL `dlsym`); macOS: native [`CAOpenGLLayer`] inserted **directly as a sublayer of the NSWindow contentView's `layer`** — gdk-macos renders GTK widgets straight into that contentView layer with no NSView subviews of its own, so an NSView wrapper for our layer would never composite (`drawInCGLContext:` fires but nothing reaches the screen); the `CAOpenGLLayer` is driven by a [`CVDisplayLink`] running on its own kernel thread so AppKit menu / popover tracking on the main run loop cannot stall video — `macos_video_cgl` (CGL pixel format + context, `OpenGL.framework` symbol loader), `macos_video_layer` (`RhinoMpvGlLayer : CAOpenGLLayer` subclass with `copyCGLContext:` / `drawInCGLContext:` overrides; `display_now()` just calls `setNeedsDisplay` so CA can pick up the frame in `kCFRunLoopCommonModes`), `macos_video_attach` (set `contentView.wantsLayer=true`, `insertSublayer:atIndex:0` so the native layer sits *under* gdk-macos's GTK rendering sublayer — combined with the **transparent GLArea** trick (`.rp-gl-native` CSS background + alpha-0 GL clear in the GLArea's render callback, see `macos_video_bundle::clear_glarea_transparent`) the GLArea region of gdk's sublayer is alpha=0 so the video below shows through, while opaque chrome (header / bottom bar) stays visible on top; mirror the `gtk::GLArea` allocation each frame via `add_tick_callback` to a Cocoa-coords frame on the layer; own the displayLink; `watch_overlay` registers a GTK widget — typically the recent grid — and `setHidden:` flips so the grid (which paints inside the same NSView) is visible whenever the layer would otherwise cover it), `macos_video_displaylink` (`CVDisplayLinkCreateWithActiveCGDisplays` + output callback that consumes a coalescing `AtomicBool` and calls `RhinoMpvGlLayer::display_now`), `macos_video_bundle` (mpv render context — update callback marks the displayLink pending, draw closure calls `mpv_render_context_render` from inside `drawInCGLContext:` with the layer's bound FBO + `MPV_RENDER_PARAM_FLIP_Y`); `linux_egl_helpers.rs` carries the cross-platform `EglState` / `egl_proc` / `GL_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING` used by the Linux render path **and** the seek-bar preview's `MpvPreviewGl` on both OSes; `mpv_persistence.rs` carries the `MpvBundle` save / load / resume / `commit_quit` impl block included alongside the platform-shaped construction code), `idle_inhibit.rs` (GTK `Application::inhibit` IDLE+SUSPEND when playing, recent grid hidden; clear on quit), `paths.rs` (XDG config, mpv `watch_later`, bundled `.vpy`, mvtools discovery — Linux: distro `vapoursynth/` + pipx vsrepo; macOS: Homebrew `lib/libmvtools.dylib`), `history.rs` (recent list via `db`), `media_probe.rs` (`remove_continue_entry` = resume clear + history remove, card data, libmpv `vo=image` + quit thumb for DB), `seek_bar_preview.rs` (popover + time; 2nd libmpv + small `GLArea` / `MpvPreviewGl` like the main [embed]), `jpeg_texture.rs` (JPEG → `GdkTexture` for recent grid; not `Texture::from_bytes` for raw bytes), `continue_undo.rs` (session snackbar **Undo**: list-remove vs **trash** + untrash), `trash_xdg.rs` (Freedesktop `Trash` locate + restore from `files/`), `sibling_advance.rs` (next/prev local file in folder + sibling order; EOF + bottom bar), `video_ext.rs` (shared `SUFFIX` list for **Open** dialog + `sibling_advance` folder scan), `recent_view.rs` (continue grid, card hover: **trash** + **remove**, spacer `dbl`→fullscreen, session undo), `time.rs` (time formatting + tests), `playback_speed.rs` (1.0/1.5/2.0/8.0× + mpv `speed` sync for header `ListBox`), `theme.rs` (CSS: dark chrome + `cursor: pointer` / `not-allowed` on controls; see `.cursor/rules/ui-cursor.mdc`), `macos_window.rs` (resolve the `NSWindow` for a `gtk::Widget` via `gdk4_macos`; toggle the standard traffic-light buttons through `NSWindow::standardWindowButton` because GTK's `set_show_*_title_buttons` is one-way on macOS).
- `tests/` — Integration tests (e.g. libmpv smoke).

## Workflow

- **Document-first**: see `.cursor/rules/document-first.mdc`. Three layers (see `docs/architecture.md`): **product behavior** (feature scenarios — portable), **architecture core** (fixed: Rust, SQLite, mpv), **platform binding** (varies per port — today: Linux / GTK / libadwaita / XDG). Each `docs/features/<NN>-<slug>.md` follows the strict template — H1, YAML front-matter (`status`, `priority`, `layers`, optional `related` / `scope`), `## Use cases`, `## Description`, `## Behavior` (single `Feature:` Gherkin block in domain language only — the single source of truth for acceptance), optional `## Notes` (the **only** place for engine APIs, UI-toolkit widgets, OS paths, env vars, persistence schema, and language types). Layer vocabulary: `ui`, `input`, `playback`, `persistence`, `storage`, `os-integration`, `build`.
- **Known UX not achieved in testing (Composer 2 Fast pass):** one-click switch between header `MenuButton` popovers — see `docs/README.md` (*Tooling note*) and `docs/features/17-window-behavior.md`. Revisit with a different model or deeper GTK review.

## Conventions

- Keep `.cursorrules` and `docs/README.md` feature list aligned with what exists in the tree.
- Prefer clear module boundaries: UI (GTK/Adwaita), mpv control, platform (DBus, portals), persistence (settings, session).
- **Quality checks:** run `cargo qcheck` (Clippy across the whole crate) before finishing. Module length is policed by `clippy::too_many_lines` (warns over ~300 lines) plus `.cursor/rules/refactor-touched-longest.mdc` (every request that edits an oversized module must shrink it in the same turn). Do not add `#[allow(clippy::…)]`—fix by refactoring (see `.cursor/rules/clippy-no-suppress.mdc`). If many modules exceed the soft limit, refactor **one file at a time**, **longest first**.
- **Complexity and module shape:** there is no Ruby-style `AbcSize` in Rust; use Clippy (see `clippy.toml`) and follow `.cursor/rules/complexity-and-module-design.mdc` (if a feature touches **>6 files** or a module is large, **prefer** smaller modules and one reason to change, without treating **300 lines** as a hard gate).
- **UI / IO timing:** prefer event subscriptions over periodic polls; see `.cursor/rules/events-over-polling.mdc`.
- Name length: prefer short, clear identifiers (2–3 words) for new types and functions, consistent with the rest of the file.
